begin_memory_text: We talked about how our days were, how our weeks were, how we were tired and that we were glad that it was the weekend. We talked about our ages, our families, and my kid (and my kid is actually a girl but I didn't want to correct her because I'm weird and sometimes can get socially awkward when I have to correct people about gender).
middle_memory_text: We discussed family, like how some families are big and small, going to school, and how the pandemic has affected daily life. We both mentioned things we had recently read or seen online or in the news about the pandemic - we also talked about movies for a short moment
end_memory_text: We talked about my tattoos, traveling, and how we both like Toronto. She talked about her fear of needles. We were at time but we both took the time to say goodnight and share well wishes with each other before signing off.
rest_of_day_open: I'm really looking forward to the weekend. It's been a long week of housework, childcare, teaching my class, trying to take care of the whole family, worrying about money, etc. It's always nice to be able to take a few days to recharge even if my day to day isn't looking that different next week.
critical_positive: I think what worked well was that we were similar in age and had shared opinions about current events, values, and even some similar interests and life experiences. I think we were open about sharing things about our personal lives enough to relate to one another and keep the conversation going. It definitely didn't feel like 25 minutes.
critical_negative: I was a little unfocused I think at times, because I had just gotten to sit down for the first time today and was really centered on unpacking and unwinding my own stuff so I don't think I was the best listener and that maybe I dominated the conversation a little bit.
